            <h2>Short Answers To Research Questions</h2>
            <h3>What is a web server?  Why would you need one?</h3>
              <p>A web server is hardware and/or software that use HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol) to serve the files that form Web pages
                 in response to user requests.
              </p>
              <a href = "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Common_questions/What_is_a_web_server" title="Mozilla" target="_blank">Reference</a>
              <p>Web servers are an integral part of the internet. Web servers provide average business owners and individuals with the 
                opportunity to use high-tech servers that make it possible to expand their outreach.
              </p>
              <a href = "https://webhostinggeeks.com/blog/what-are-web-servers-and-why-are-they-needed/" title="WebHostingGeeks" target="_blank">Reference</a>
            <h3>Explain why getting a domain name is not enough to put your site up on the web.</h3>
              <p>Registering a domain name doesn't automatically create a website.  You also need to build the website and host it.</p>
              <a href = "https://www.godaddy.com/help/whats-the-difference-between-a-domain-and-a-website-16574" title="GoDaddy" target="_blank">Reference</a>
              <h3>What service does a website hosting company provide?</h3>
              <p>A website hosting company provides the technologies (hardware and software) and services needed for the website  
                 to be stored and viewed in on the internet. </p>
              <a href = "https://www.website.com/beginnerguide/webhosting/6/1/what-is-web-hosting?.ws" title="Website Beginners Guide" target="_blank">Reference</a>   
              <h3>What are the most important characteristics to look for in selecting a good web hosting company?</h3>
              <ul>
                    <li>Price</li>
                    <li>Focus Areas Or Specialties</li>
                    <li>Technical Support</li>
                    <li>Features And Add-ons</li>
                    <li>Quality Hardware</li>
                    <li>Company Reputation And Customer Satisfaction</li>
                    <li>Email Features</li>
                    <li>Control Panel And User Interface</li>
                    <li>Room To Grow</li>
                </ul>
              <a href = "https://www.shoutmeloud.com/4-things-to-consider-choosing-web-host-company.html" title="ShoutMeLoud" target="_blank">Reference</a>
              <h3>Research companies that provide website hosting plans. On average, what is the price range (price per month) for hosting a website?</h3>
              <p>Average for basic shared web hosting for one website = $3.80 (based on the following 3 companies)</p>
              <a href = "https://www.bluehost.com/web-hosting/signup" title="BlueHost" target="_blank">BlueHost -> $2.95 per month</a>
              <a href = "https://www.hostgator.com/promo/top10best?clickid=wwDVcLUn1xyJWKKwUx0Mo34VUkn1GKSlzWJ1yw0&irgwc=1&affpat=1&mpid=34020" title="WebGator" target="_blank">WebGator -> $2.75 per month</a>
              <a href = "https://www.networksolutions.com/hosting?clickid=UakyiQXC%253AxyJT4NwUx0Mo34nUkn1GZ15zWJ1yw0&iradid=596012&irpid=34020&sharedid=&source=IR&siteid=662&channelid=P61C662S645N0B9A1D9E0000V100&promo=HOSTINGSAVE20" title="NetworkSolutions" target="_blank">NetworkSolutions -> $5.69 per month</a>
              <h3>What are the most important features for you when reviewing a hosting plan?</h3>
              <ul>
                    <li>Number Of Websites</li>
                    <li>Website Storage Space</li>
                    <li>Bandwidth</li>
                    <li>SSL Certificate</li>
                    <li>Email Addresses</li>
                    <li>Cost</li>
                </ul>
        </section>
